The course will introduce students to a subset of advances and current topics in the area of computer technology. The students will explore the topics and give presentations along with the opportunity to see some currently deployed systems in Estonian industry and scientific institutes.Objectives/eesmärkid:  * To give an overview of the state of the art in a subset of areas in computer technology * To have the students explore and present these technologies * To introduce some of the local industry and the systems they have currently in useLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of this course the participants will have improved in: * preparing and presenting an overview of new/emerging technology; * understanding some of the potential advances and important questions of tomorrow in the field; * presenting "the clever idea" behind a fresh technology in a compact manner; * having knowledge of the local companies and research centres either developing or deploying the discussed technologies; * collaboratively working on a larger document using versioning tool Git.
